{
  "doc_id": "9581",
  "text": "Drosophila melanogaster is an important model for the identification and study of genes that have relevance to mammalian cardiovascular development and function [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] . The abdominal heart in Drosophila consists of individual cardiomyocytes that form a contractile syncytium and pump haemolymph from the abdomen, through the thorax towards the head (see schematic in Figure 1A ).",
